<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Read Logister's privacy policy for how account data, application event data, cookies, analytics, and security services are handled." %>
<% content_for :canonical_path, privacy_path %>
<% content_for :og_type, "article" %>
<% content_for :json_ld, json_ld({
  "@context" => "https://schema.org",
  "@type" => "WebPage",
  "name" => "Logister Privacy Policy",
  "url" => absolute_url_for(privacy_path),
  "description" => "Privacy policy for Logister's hosted service."
}) %>

<div class="marketing-home legal-page">
  <section class="legal-hero" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up" style="view-transition-name: public-hero; view-transition-class: public-panel;">
    <p class="hero-kicker">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="hero-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="hero-copy max-w-3xl">
      This policy explains what information Logister collects, how it is used,
      and what controls you have when using the hosted service and related APIs.
    </p>
    <p class="legal-updated"><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 2, 2026</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-summary-grid" style="view-transition-name: public-stats; view-transition-class: public-panel;">
    <article class="about-pill-card" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up">
      <p class="stat-label">Account data</p>
      <p class="about-pill-value">Email, profile, projects, memberships</p>
    </article>
    <article class="about-pill-card" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up" data-reveal-delay-value="80">
      <p class="stat-label">Application event data</p>
      <p class="about-pill-value">Errors, logs, metrics, context payloads</p>
    </article>
    <article class="about-pill-card" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up" data-reveal-delay-value="140">
      <p class="stat-label">Security and analytics</p>
      <p class="about-pill-value">Consent-gated tools where enabled</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-card" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up" style="view-transition-name: public-workflow; view-transition-class: public-panel;">
    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Scope</h2>
      <p>
        This policy applies to the Logister website, hosted application, and hosted APIs at
        <code>logister.org</code>. Self-hosted Logister deployments are controlled by the
        organization operating that deployment and should publish their own privacy terms.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <p>
        We collect information needed to provide the service, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Account details you provide, such as email address, password credentials, profile name, and account settings.</li>
        <li>Project and team information, including project names, memberships, API keys, and integration configuration.</li>
        <li>Application event data sent through Logister clients or the ingest API, such as errors, logs, metrics, transactions, check-ins, stack traces, request details, headers, query parameters, and cookies when your integration sends them.</li>
        <li>Technical data generated by site and API usage, such as IP address, browser, device, timestamps, pages viewed, request metadata, and diagnostic logs.</li>
        <li>Messages you send us for support, security, or account questions.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Application event data</h2>
      <p>
        Logister receives the data your applications choose to send. You are responsible
        for configuring SDKs, filters, and payloads so they do not include secrets,
        credentials, payment data, or sensitive personal information unless you have a
        lawful reason to send that data and have protected it appropriately.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>How we use information</h2>
      <p>
        We use information to operate Logister, authenticate accounts, process
        application events, show dashboards and project history, send transactional
        emails, troubleshoot service reliability, prevent abuse, improve product quality,
        and respond to support or legal requests.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <p>
        Logister uses cookies and similar technologies for sessions, authentication,
        security, consent preferences, and optional analytics. Analytics scripts for
        Google Analytics or Cloudflare Web Analytics load only when configured for the
        deployment and allowed by the consent banner. Read the
        <%= link_to "Cookie Policy", cookies_path %> for details.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Service providers</h2>
      <p>
        We may share information with service providers that help us run Logister, such
        as hosting and infrastructure providers, email delivery providers, bot-protection
        and security services, analytics providers, and professional advisers. We do not
        sell personal information.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use reasonable administrative and technical safeguards to protect data, such
        as encrypted transport, credential hashing, scoped API keys, parameter filtering,
        and access controls. No internet transmission or storage system can be guaranteed
        to be fully secure.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep account and project data while your account is active or as needed to
        provide the service, resolve disputes, maintain security, and comply with legal
        obligations. Event data is kept for the period supported by the product or your
        deployment settings. Backups, audit logs, and operational logs may persist for a
        limited period after primary data is changed or removed.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <p>
        You can update account details, rotate or revoke API keys, configure what your
        applications send, manage cookie choices, and request account or data deletion.
        Some data may need to be retained where required for security, service integrity,
        or legal obligations.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>International processing</h2>
      <p>
        Information may be processed in countries where we or our service providers
        operate. By using the hosted service, you understand that data may be transferred
        outside your state, province, or country.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy as Logister changes. When we make material changes, we
        will update the date above and, where appropriate, provide additional notice in
        the product or by email.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions, contact
        <code>support@logister.org</code>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="marketing-cta" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up" style="view-transition-name: public-cta; view-transition-class: public-panel;">
    <div>
      <p class="workflow-kicker">Related pages</p>
      <h2>Need legal or product details?</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <%= link_to "Cookie policy", cookies_path, class: "hero-btn hero-btn-primary" %>
      <%= link_to "Terms of use", terms_path, class: "hero-btn hero-btn-secondary" %>
      <%= link_to "About Logister", about_path, class: "hero-btn hero-btn-secondary" %>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
